metadata.editComments: Changed the numerals to more easily understood degrees and added C# G# throughout which gave E6 D#7/11 and Dmaj7#11

metadata.song: God Put A Smile Upon Your Face
metadata.editComments: Changed the analysis to the perspective of A Major. This is because there is actually a ringing G# and C# in the high strings over the whole chorus. This makes Amaj7, E6, F#add2. It could also be viewed from A Major which honestly might be the actual tonic, but making the F# chord into a II (V/V) in E rather than a VI (V/II) in A seemed easier to understand.
